UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1740
1 AN ACT relating to physician continuing medical education.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 311.601 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The board may promulgate[adopt] reasonable administrative[rules and] regulations
5 to effectuate and implement[ the provisions of] KRS 311.550 to 311.620, including
6 but not limited to administrative regulations designed to ensure the continuing
7 professional competency of present and future licensees. As an adjunct to the power
8 conferred upon the board by this section, the board may require licensees to submit
9 to interrogation as to the nature and extent of their postgraduate medical education
10 and to require licensees found to be deficient in their efforts to keep abreast of new
11 methods and technology, to obtain additional instruction and training therein.
12 (2) As part of the continuing medical education which the board adopts to ensure
13 continuing professional competency of present and future licensees, the board shall
14 ensure that:
15 (a) Current practicing pediatricians, including those certified in medicine and
16 pediatrics, radiologists, family practitioners, and those physicians practicing
17 in an emergency medicine or urgent care setting, demonstrate completion of a
18 one (1) time course of at least one (1) hour of continuing medical education
19 approved by the board and covering the recognition and prevention of
20 pediatric abusive head trauma, as defined in KRS 620.020, prior to December
21 31, 2017;[ and]
22 (b) Future practicing pediatricians, including those certified in medicine and
23 pediatrics, radiologists, family practitioners, and those physicians who will
24 practice in an emergency medicine or urgent care setting, demonstrate
25 completion of a one (1) time course of at least one (1) hour of continuing
26 medical education, or its equivalent, approved by the board and covering the
27 recognition and prevention of pediatric abusive head trauma, as defined in
