UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1740
1 KRS 620.020, within five (5) years of licensure. Future practicing
2 pediatricians, including those certified in medicine and pediatrics,
3 radiologists, family practitioners, and those physicians who will practice in an
4 emergency medicine or urgent care setting may apply pediatric abusive head
5 trauma curriculum taught in their medical school education to count towards
6 the required one (1) hour of continuing medical education; and
7 (c) Current practicing physicians demonstrate completion of at least three (3)
8 hours of continuing medical education every three (3) years that is approved
9 by the board and covers the recognition and treatment of mental health
10 issues, including but not limited to emotional, psychological, and social
11 well-being issues and mental health disorders.
